news.title: Court appoints new directors of Oberoi Hotels & Oberoi Properties amid inheritance dispute
news.para: The appointments were confirmed during an annual general meeting on Tuesday, people said. The appointments were made abiding by terms of a consent order passed by the Delhi High Court earlier in the day.

news.title: Bengaluru metro's extended green line operation may launch from November 6
news.para: Chief PRO of BMRCL said, "We are working on fixing train schedules and deploying staff at the three new stations. We will share details on operating trains till Madavara on Wednesday."

news.title: M3M Group's directors seek halt of trial in 'cash for favour' scam
news.para: The M3M directors – Basant Bansal and Pankaj Bansal – submitted that the trial should be halted as the Haryana anti-corruption bureau (ACB) was yet to conclude the investigations into the case linked to it.

news.title: Telangana RERA imposes Rs 15 lakh penalty on Jayabheri Properties
news.para: The complainants claimed ownership of approximately 28 acres of land in Puppalaguda village in Gandipet mandal in Rangareddy District. They filed suits for a declaration of title, which is pending before the III additional district judge, Rangareddy, LB Nagar.

news.title: Yes Bank's Rs 4,733 crore loan for DHFL was diverted to builders in Mumbai: CBI
news.para: The CBI recently filed the fresh supplementary charge sheet against 41 accused, including Indiabulls Housing Finance, builders Shahid Balwa, Vinod Goneka, Avinash Bhosale Sanjay Chhabriaa and companies linked to them.

news.title: Easy Home Finance secures $35 million funding led by Claypond Capital and others
news.para: Existing investors Xponentia Capital, Finsight Ventures, Harbourfront Capital, and Pegasus India Evolving Opportunities Fund, also participated in the round.

news.title: Telangana RERA orders Vijetha Infra to refund buyer and imposes penalty for project violations
news.para: In her complaint, G Swetha said an MoU was signed with the company in March 2020 for buying a commercial space (250 sq ft) in Sensation Vijetha Mall.

news.title: RR Kabel's MD, family buys two flats worth Rs 198 crore in Mumbai's Worli
news.para: The apartments spread a total of over 13,809 sq ft area in one of the wings of the tower on Dr. Annie Besant Road are on the 62nd floor. Kabra has bought the apartment along with his wife, son, and daughter in law.

news.title: IHCL acquires majority stake in Ambuja Neotia Group's Rajscape Hotels
news.para: IHCL in an exchange filing stated that its board has approved the execution of an agreement to acquire about 55 per cent equity shares "for an amount not exceeding Rs 18 crore in Rajscape Hotels Private Limited".

news.title: Arvind SmartSpaces to raise Rs 400 crore
news.para: The board of Arvind SmartSpaces also approved increase in authorised share capital of the company from Rs 50 crore divided into five crore equity shares of Rs 10 each to Rs 70 crore divided into seven crore equity shares of Rs 10 each.

news.title: Berger Paints India's net profit dips 7.61% in Q2 FY25
news.para: Berger Paints India's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 2,795.71 crore in Q2 FY25, a growth of 0.47 per cent from Rs 2,782.58 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Aptus Value Housing Finance's net profit up 22.94% in Q2 FY25
news.para: Aptus Value Housing Finance's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 435.54 crore in Q2 FY25, a growth of 26 per cent from Rs 345.66 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: States not empowered to take over all private properties for distribution to serve common good: SC
news.para: A nine-judge bench headed by Chief Justice DY Chandrachud, however, said states can stake claim over private properties in certain cases.

news.title: Bengaluru: Property owners face hurdles in obtaining  e-khatas due to system issue
news.para: The e-khata initiative, designed to streamline property registration and enhance the security of the documents, has faced numerous software issues, delaying the issuance of the digital property records, BBMP officials acknowledge.

news.title: Kerala government to decide on new alignment of Thiruvananthapuram metro this month
news.para: Kochi Metro Rail Ltd (KMRL), the project executing agency, submitted the preliminary study report based on the new alignment from Kazhakkoottam to East Fort via Sreekaryam and Medical College, as proposed by state govt.

news.title: DTCP demolish nine illegal colonies across Sultanpur and Farrukhnagar
news.para: The operation, under the jurisdiction of Farrukhnagar police station, was conducted to curb illegal structures, road networks and other unapproved buildings.

news.title: Indore district committee receives public feedback on collector's guideline hike
news.para: The committee, which initiated the process as mid-term revision of the collector's guideline, proposed increasing the guideline value for property in 469 locations across the district.

news.title: Delhi civic body launches digital portal to boost property tax collection
news.para: While the data collected will be processed further for generating information and collecting tax, the department will conduct a weekly review of the zonal inspectors based on the report or date submitted online.

news.title: Kolkata metro’s orange line phase II extension deadline revised to March 2025
news.para: RVNL, the implementing agency that was chasing a Dec 2024 deadline to complete the 4km extension beyond Metropolitan on EM Bypass to Sector V on Salt Lake Bypass, has acknowledged that it will not be possible to complete the work by this year-end

news.title: Bhopal property prices set to rise 5% to 250% in 230 locations
news.para: According to the proposal property prices enhancement or collectorate rate will surge at 230 locations instead of 243 locations. There will also be a 5% reduction at the proposed 230 locations as well.
